import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['departure_delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['departure_delay'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['departure_delay'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='departure_delay', bins=50, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['departure_delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['departure_delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Departure Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin_airport'].value_counts()
    chart = sns.barplot(x=origin_counts.index, y=origin_counts.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most common origin airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Origin Airports', loc='upper right', labels=origin_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the proportion of cancelled and not cancelled flights
    cancelled_counts = data['cancelled'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    
    # Create a pie chart
    plt.pie(cancelled_counts, labels=['Not Cancelled', 'Cancelled'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight cancellations?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Not Cancelled', 'Cancelled'], loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
